I will not be recounting it here, but I recommend reading through it if you want a clearer understanding of the data that is being processed, or the required structure of any data set you might wish to input into this model.

WARNING: This next section of code will take several days to run

It is clear that SLOPE is not a significant covariate. Here, we re-fit mf04c.glmssn0 with REML (the default, so the EstMeth =ML argument can be dropped), along with a few more covariance structures: This above may or may not be true for our data. For the purposes of following the vignette we will assume that it is.

ssn_mainc.glmssn1 <- glmssn(TWAT ~ ELEV, ssn_mainc,
CorModels = c("Exponential.tailup", "Exponential.taildown"),
addfunccol = "afvArea", EstMeth = "ML")
